Text.Value: *The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
Your body will attract scavengers. Should I bury you?
Would you like me to craft you a stunning tale? Lock your memory in legend forever?
Are there any rites you'd like performed over your body?
Took me here... put something in my eye...
They put something in my eye too. Can we get rid of it?
Guiding my cart... shadow fell... tentacle grabbed me...
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
No... took everyone... peasants... lords... took them all...
Do you know why any of us were taken?

Synopsis: You speak with the dead soul of a merchant, who was kidnapped by the mindflayers and died in the crash. The player can offer to help bury the body or perform any last rites, but they'll be rebuked by the spirit.
